title: Highest Vitamin A Supplementation Coverage
description: In 2022, Guinea achieved a remarkable Vitamin A supplementation coverage rate of 97% among children aged 6-59 months, showcasing its commitment to child health.

title: Lowest Percentage of Female Secondary Education Teachers
description: As of 2021, only 5.8% of secondary education teachers in Guinea were female, highlighting a significant gender disparity in the education sector.

title: Lowest Physicians per 1,000 People
description: In 2022, Guinea had just 0.021 physicians per 1,000 people, indicating a critical shortage of medical professionals in the country.

title: Minimal Contribution of Travel Services to Service Imports
description: Travel services accounted for only 1.1% of Guinea's service imports in 2022, reflecting a limited role in the country's service sector.

title: Minimal International Tourism Receipts
description: In 2020, international tourism receipts contributed a mere 0.014% to Guinea's total exports, underscoring the underdeveloped tourism industry.

title: High Financial Intermediary Services Value
description: Guinea's Financial Intermediary Services Indirectly Measured reached 3,656,694,434,200 LCU in 2022, indicating a robust financial sector.
